<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="189" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1821,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1929,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="189">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male macrophthalmous; head with six vertexal tufts of bristles fused to form continuous transverse row; aedeagus with large apical plate with concave apical margin, base of median lobe rapidly narrowing toward basal foramen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3711754" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3711754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3711754/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="190" startId="3.[151,264,1382,1407]" targetBox="[214,1361,181,1356]" targetPageId="3">
